Spell:  Meditate [9101]

Usage:  USE 9101

Required aura:  none
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

The magician enters a restful trance which regenerates body, mind
and current aura level.  Current aura level will rise by one point.
Meditation may allow current aura to rise above maximum aura by one
point.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Forge auraculum [9102]

Usage:  USE 9102 <aura-level> "Name"

Required aura:   as specified by caster
Required items:  100 gold, 5 mithril
Time to cast:    fourteen days

Forge a magical auraculum, giving it the specified name.

   An auraculum is a magical artifact which concentrates and amplifies
   a mage's power.  A permanent investment of maximum aura is made when
   constructing the auraculum.  The artifact doubles the invested aura.
   However, since a portion of the mage's pneuma has been bound in the
   auraculum, it is important to safeguard it from being lost or stolen.

In addition to depleting the caster's current aura level, the specified
aura amount will be permanently removed from the magician's maximum aura
rating.  The new object, while possessed by its maker, will augment the
mage's maximum aura rating by twice the amount of aura invested in its
creation.

Creation of an auraculum also grants knowledge of the Advanced sorcery
magical skill category.  Advanced sorcery may not be learned in any
other way.

Example:

   A mage of current aura level 10, maximum aura 10 who issues
   USE @@@@ 5 "Ring of power" will be reduced to current aura level 5,
   maximum aura level 5.  However, the new artifact will add 10 points
   to the maximum aura rating of its creator, but only while it is in
   his possession.

    1: > use @@@@ 5 "Ring of power"
    1: Attempt to forge an auraculum.
       ...
   14: Created Ring of power [js80].
   14: Learned Advanced sorcery [166].

       Current aura:   5
       Maximum aura:   15 (5+10)
 
Characters other than the auraculum's creator do not receive an aura
bonus from possession of the object.

Since the mage has bound a portion of his aura into the artifact, its
destruction would deal him an instant, fatal blow.  Thus, the creator
of such an object should use all means to prevent it from being lost
or stolen.  However, magical items of such power are hard to destroy.
An auraculum may only be destroyed in the province in which it was
created.

This spell may only be used once.  A magician may only create one
auraculum during his lifetime.

The creator of the artifact may change its name later with the
NAME order.  The object must be possessed in order to rename it.

   > name js80 "Wooden staff"
   Ring of power [js80] will now be known as Wooden staff [js80].

-----------------------------





It is unlikely that the item could be harmed
outside of the region in which it was created.

Since the mage has bound a portion of his aura into the artifact,
its destruction would cause him to instantly perish.  Thus, the
creator of such an object should take all means to prevent it from
being lost or stolen.  However, magical items of such power are
hard to destroy.  It is unlikely that the item could be harmed
outside of the region in which it was created.


   In other words, the cast removes 5 points of the mage's maximum
   aura rating.  The artifact expands it by 10, to 15.  However, if 
   the artifact is lost or stolen, the mage will be reduced again to
   a maximum aura level of 5.



   For example, successful cast of USE @@@@ 5 "Ring of power" will
   create an artifact which adds 10 points to the effective maximum
   aura rating of its creator, while it is in his possession.


Creates a magical artifact, giving it the specified name.

In addition to depleting the caster's current aura level,
the specified aura amount will be permanently removed from
the magician's maximum aura rating.

	For example, a mage of current aura level 10, maximum aura
	level 10 who issues USE 9102 5 "Ring of power" will be
	reduced to current aura level 5, maximum aura level 5.

The new magical artifact will be unique, and uniquely useful to its
creator.  While possessed, the artifact will augment its creator's
maximum aura rating by an amount twice as much as the amount invested
in its creation.

	Continuing the above example, a successful cast of
	USE 9102 5 "Ring of power" will create an artifact which
	will add 10 points to the effective maximum aura rating
	of its creator, while possessed.

	Note that cast permanently diminishes the mage's maximum
	aura level by 5.  The artifact expands it by 10, to 15.
	However, if the artifact is lost or stolen, the mage
	will be reduced again to a maximum aura rating of 5.

Other characters will not receive as much benefit from the item,
perhaps gaining an aura boost of only one point, regardless of
the object's power in the hands of its creator.

Since the mage has bound a portion of his aura into the artifact,
its destruction would cause him to instantly perish.  Thus, the
creator of such an object should take all means to prevent it from
being lost or stolen.  However, magical items of such power are
hard to destroy.  It is unlikely that the item could be harmed
outside of the region in which it was created.

This spell may only be used once.  A magician may only create one
auraculum during his lifetime.

The creator of the artifact may change its name later with the
NAME order.  The object must be possessed in order to rename it.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Expand auraculum power [9103]

Usage:  USE 9103 <artifact> <item>

Required aura:  10
Required item:  another magician's auraculum
Time to cast:   fourteen days

Used by a mage who has constructed an artifact with [9102], this
spell will increase the artifact's power.  The artifact from another
mage must be obtained and specified in the usage of the spell.

The other mage's artifact will be destroyed, and its trapped aural
power will be added to the caster's artifact.  The creator of the
destroyed artifact will be killed by this spell.

	For example, a mage who has constructed an artifact [781]
	for himself obtains another magician's artifact [929].
	The spell USE 9103 781 929 would destroy object [929] (and
	kill its creator), and add [929]'s power to [781].

Any spells trapped in the destroyed artifact will be lost.  They
will not be transferred to the mage's artifact.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Sacrifice noble [9104]

Usage:  USE 9104 <character>

Required aura:  none
Required item:  Specify a prisoner to be killed
Time to cast:   seven days

The necromancer will conduct a ritual in which the designated
prisoner is sacrificed.  The ritual will trap the unfortunate
victim's life force, which will serve to infuse the caster with
aura.  The mage's current aura level will increase by 10 points
upon the noble's death.

The body of the noble is consumed by fire during the ritual.

-----------------------------

Spell:  View current aura level of others [9105]

Usage:  USE 9105

Required aura:  2
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

The current aura level of other mages present in the same location
as the caster will be shown.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Speed casting of next spell [9106]

Usage: USE 9106 <amount>

Required aura:  amount as specified above
Required item:
Time to cast:   four days

The mage trades aura for time.  The time necessary to cast
the next spell will be reduced by the amount of aura invested
in the cast of [9106].

For example, a mage who issued USE 9106 5 would lose five current
aura points.  Whatever spell the mage casts next will take five days
less than it normally would.

-----------------------------

Spell: Reveal creator of magical artifact [9108]

Usage: USE 9108 <artifact> [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points of aura
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

Reveal who forged a magical artifact.  The artifact in
question must be possessed by the caster.

The artifact may be shrouded against magical inspection.
If so, a greater amount of aura must be specified with
@@@@ than was used to apply the shroud.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Reveal where artifact was created [9109]

Usage:  USE 9109 <artifact> [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

Reveal the location in which a magical magical artifact was forged.
The artifact in question must be possessed by the caster.

Some magical artifacts may only be destroyed in the location where
they were constructed.

The artifact may be shrouded against magical inspection.  If so,
a greater amount of aura must be specified with @@@@ than was
used to apply the shroud.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Cloak creator of artifact [9110]

Usage:  USE @@@@ <artifact> [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

Inhibit the ability of another mage to learn the identity of the
creator of the specified magical artifact.  The artifact must be
in the inventory of the caster.

The more aura used, the more difficult it will be for another
mage to overcome the magical cloaking.

The default aura to use is one point.
Multiple casts of @@@@ on the same artifact are additive.

-----------------------------

Spell: Cloak region of artifact creation [9111]

Usage: USE @@@@ <artifact> [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

Inhibit the ability of another mage to learn the region in which
the specified magical artifact was created.  The artifact must
be in the inventory of the caster.

The more aura used, the more difficult it will be for another
mage to overcome the magical cloaking.

The default aura to use is one point.
Multiple casts of @@@@ on the same artifact are additive.

-----------------------------

Spell:  Cloak magical aura [9112]

Usage:  USE 9112

Required aura:  three points
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days
Duration:       thirty-seven days

Prevents other mages from sensing the caster's current
aura level for the duration of the spell.

