Spell:  Shroud region from magical scry [9142]

Usage:  USE 9142 [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points, as given
Required item:
Time to cast:   three days

Creates a magical shroud over the mage's current location.  The
shroud hinders attempts by distant mages to view the region by
magical scrying.

The shroud is invested with magical aura.  A mage attempting to
view the region from a distance with a scry spell must expend a
greater amount of aura than the shroud possess to succeed.

The shroud loses one point of aura at the end of each month.
Successive uses of 9142 are additive; USE 9142 1 followed by
USE 9142 3 will result in a region shroud with an aura of
four points.

The default aura to use is one point.

