Spell:  Project next magic cast [9172]

Usage:  USE 9172 <location> [aura]

Required aura:  one or more points, as given
Required item:
Time to cast:   seven days

Location checks for the next spell cast within the Magic [160]
category will be made from the given location, instead of the
location the mage is in.  This effectively allows the mage to
cast a Magic spell anywhere in the Olympian world.

Sufficient aura must be specified at the time 9172 is cast to
overcome any magical shrouds in effect at the target location.
A location shroud check is not made when the projected spell
is actually cast.

