Spell Casting Limitations
-------------------------

Spells may only be cast n times per turn
	simpler
	but collision problem at beginning of month

Spells may only be cast within n days of one another
	more complex
	more random -- hard to tell when it's safe to cast a spell

Why?

1.
spell's power to cause effect in physical world comes from their
innate patters in the aural plane.  Casting a spell depeletes the
pattern of energy.  The stronger the spell, the longer it takes to
regenerate.

2.
All spells are fundamentally based on expressing the true name of
the desired effect in the aural plane.

No two magicians can cast the same spell at the same time.
(fail after one day for fairness?)
(phys: cast-attempt list in spell entity)

Basic:  Prevail over contesters / competitors for next cast

Once cast, a spell requires an amount of time to regenerate.
Each spell lists how many days it takes to regenerate.


Illusion:  Prophecy arrivals to this location
Gatecraft:  Inhibit jumps to region
Gatecraft:  Inhibit jumps from region

Spell:  Reflect cast (given who and spell, reflects cast back on them)

